// Design Editor Refs
// Module-level singletons for non-serializable design editor objects.
// Kept outside Zustand because they hold WASM handles, GPU resources, and mutable data structures.

The singleton refs object holds: graph (SceneGraph), undo (UndoManager), canvasKit (CanvasKit | null),
renderer (SkiaRenderer | null), textEditor (TextEditor | null).
graph and undo are always initialized; the others start as null until the canvas is ready.

FUNCTION getEditorRefs() -> EditorRefs                                  EXPORT
  Return the singleton refs object.

---

FUNCTION initEditorRefs(ck, renderer)                                   EXPORT
  CALLS: TextEditor (text-editor)
  Store the CanvasKit instance and renderer in refs.
  Create a new TextEditor with the CanvasKit instance and attach the renderer to it.

---

FUNCTION destroyEditorRefs()                                            EXPORT
  Call renderer.destroy() if present.
  Clear renderer, canvasKit, and textEditor to null.
  Reset graph to a new empty SceneGraph.
  Clear the undo history.

---

FUNCTION resetSceneGraph()                                              EXPORT
  CALLS: SceneGraph (scene-graph)
  Replace graph with a new empty SceneGraph.
  Clear the undo history.

---

FUNCTION setSceneGraph(graph)                                           EXPORT
  Replace the current graph with the provided SceneGraph.
  Clear the undo history.
